This paper deals with algorithms for solving quantified Boolean formulas, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the integration of the CEGAR principle, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of inference rules and analysis of different cases suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the experimental evaluation of the performance of the algorithm suggests a focus on computational complexity (cs.CC).
